text: Mateusz Piechowski (born 1 March 1995) is a Polish handball player who plays for Wisła Płock and the Polish national team.EHF profile He was chosen to participate at the 2016 Summer Olympics in Rio de Janeiro, in the men's handball tournament, but failed to make it to the final squad. ==References== Category:1995 births Category:Living people Category:Polish male handball players
